metadata.title: Alaska National Parks Boundaries

creators.name: National Park Service, Division of Resources, Geographical Information Services

metadata.description: Data Type: Boundaries;   This data set depicts the administrative boundaries of all Alaska lands administered by the U.S. National Park System. These lands include all park, preserve, monument, current and proposed wilderness. This database was constructed for the National Park Service, Alaska Regional Office Division of Planning to digitally store and represent administrative boundaries and to produce tabular acreage calculations of these administrative areas.
